title: Cambridge History of Greek and Roman Warfare Vol 1 - 2
description:
Volume 1, Greece, The Hellenistic World and the Rise of Rome 
Volume 2, Rome from the Late Republic to the Late Empire 

0521782732, 0521782740 | edition 2007 | PDF | 1198 pages | 17 MB

Warfare was the single biggest preoccupation of historians in antiquity. In recent decades fresh textual interpretations, numerous new archaeological discoveries and a much broader analytical focus emphasizing social, economic, political and cultural approaches have transformed our understanding of ancient warfare
